# 🛡️ DevShield
### Self-Improving AI Codebase Auditor & Security-First IDE

DevShield is a **browser-based, AI-powered development environment** that combines intelligent code editing with **real-time security auditing**. Unlike traditional AI tools that treat code as plain text, DevShield understands code as **structured logic** using graphs.

---

## 🚀 Why DevShield?

Standard AI tools (like GitHub Copilot) often generate fixes that break logic or miss vulnerabilities. DevShield solves this by grounding AI in **code structure + data flow**.

| AI Limitation        | DevShield Solution                                      | Technology Used           |
|----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Syntax Errors        | Validates patches against **AST** before suggesting     | Tree-sitter, Monaco       |
| Location Errors      | Injects fixes at exact logical node                     | Code Property Graph (CPG) |
| Semantic Drift       | Ensures logic consistency via **CFG tracking**          | Control Flow Graph        |
| Misleading Fixes     | Verifies secure flow using **Taint Analysis**           | Data Flow Graph           |
| Partial Fixes        | Detects cross-file issues via repo-wide analysis        | GNN Embeddings            |
| Human Intent Gap     | Learns from accepted/rejected fixes                     | Feedback Loop             |

---

## 🧠 Core Innovation: Graph-First AI

DevShield converts code into a **Code Property Graph (CPG)**, combining:

- **AST (Abstract Syntax Tree)** → Syntax structure  
- **CFG (Control Flow Graph)** → Execution paths  
- **PDG (Program/Data Flow Graph)** → Data dependencies  

A **Graph Neural Network (GNN)** analyzes this structure to detect:
- Unsafe data flows
- Injection vulnerabilities
- Logic anomalies

